en_184906_0	Arjun Aloysius and Kasun Palisena further remanded...
en_184906_1	Owner of Perpetual Treasuries Limited, Arjun Aloysius and its CEO Kasun Palisena have been further remanded until 15 th of March.
en_184906_2	They were produced before Colombo Fort Magistrate this morning (Mar. 02).
en_184906_3	Aloysius and Palisena were arrested by the Criminal Investigation Department on 4 th of February as they have been mentioned as suspects in the Central Bank bond scam.
en_184906_4	The first accused in the scam, former Central Bank Governor Arjuna Mahendran has evaded arrest and it was reported he is not available even at his Singapore address.
en_184906_5	Meanwhile, the Attorney General is planning to take action against Mahendran through Interpol if he chooses to disregard the notice issued against him.
en_184906_6	The Fort Magistrate Lanka Jayaratne issued the notice on Mahendran to report to the CID and record a statement before 15th of February.
